@NODE "introduction" "Atoms-X - Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

Atoms-X is my own take on the classic PD game Atoms. Something reminded me of Atoms a few weeks ago, so I went home and started writing my own version.
The original version was on a magazing coverdisk about 20 years ago, and I'm sure I still have that disk somewhere, but I decided it would be better to start from scratch with a modern, Workbench-compatible version which will work on OS4 as well as OS3 machines.

Atoms-X is a board game in which players take it in turn to try and eliminate the opponents and be the only player with pieces remaining on the board. Enemy pieces are taken by filling an adjacent cell with atoms until it is overfull and bursts, overflowing into the enemy's cell and taking their atoms over. This can lead to large chain reactions, often swinging the game dramatically towards to end.

@{"Read more about how to play Atoms-X" LINK "playing"}
