@NODE "requirements" "Atoms-X - Requirements"

@{b}Requirements@{ub}

Atoms-X has the following requirements:
  - 68020 or better
  - About 1.2MB free chip RAM on AGA classics, 400k free Chip RAM on OCS/ECS classics, or 4MB on NGs or classics with graphics cards and AHI
  - AmigaOS3 or AmigaOS4

Atoms-X has been tested on the following machines and found to work fine:
  - AmigaOne XE-G4, OS4.1 update 6
  - Amiga 1200 060/66, 192MB, Voodoo 3-3000, OS3.9
  - Amiga 1200 030/50, 32MB, AGA, OS3.1 & OS3.9
  - iBook G4, MorphOS 3.3

If a graphics card isn't detected, the user can choose a screenmode when Atoms-X starts.

AHI is used for sound effects, but if it's not found, reduced-quality sound is used instead through the standard classic chipset.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "installation" "Atoms-X - Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

Atoms-X doesn't really need "installation" - just unpack it and put the drawer wherever you want it. And if you're reading this you've already sorted out the first bit!

Alternative icons (OS4 32-bit and NewIcons) are included as well if you'd prefer to use either of those... Just copy over the icon if you like.

